               <p class="geedo-p">The primary job of a blog is to possess content in the form of some tangible information that cover the most commonly searched topics on google, that relate to your product, or services.<br>
                 Blog posts are meant to provide valuable information to people in a way that's free and easy to read. Blogs should have textual content as well as visual content to educate and captivate, not only your audience, but carefully applying keyword research to your important title tags, h1-h6 tags, and alt-text attributes for image files, etc...To captivate the google search engine before other content that may not be as "properly filed" as your online content will be in the theoretical filing cabinet of google.<br><br> It's the first step to building trust with readers so that you can turn them into customers in the future.
                A blog is a type of website where the content is presented in reverse chronological order (newer content appear first). Blog content is often referred to as entries or “blog posts”.

                Blogs are typically run by an individual or a small group of people (businesses and developers) to present information in a conversational style
               </p>
